🔥 6. Important Concepts
🧹 Dirty Pages
Modified data in RAM not yet on disk

🔄 Writeback
Triggered by:

Memory pressure

fsync()

Periodic kernel flush

📍 Inode
Stores:

File size

Permissions

Block pointers

NOT filename (that’s in directory entry)

📁 Dentry (Directory Cache)
Maps:

filename → inode
📦 Superblock
Contains:

Filesystem type

Block size

Total blocks

🧠 7. File Offset → Sector Mapping
Very important internally:

file offset (bytes)
   ↓
logical block = offset / block_size
   ↓
filesystem mapping (ext4)
   ↓
physical block number
   ↓
sector = physical_block × (block_size / 512)
👉 Sector conversion happens in:

Filesystem + block layer

